rComments: Really terrible professor. The textbook is your only Saviour, and really, it's the lesser of two evils. This was the most painful class I've ever taken. It's not that the material is that bad, but the professor doesn't have a clue on how to lecture.

Really great guy! New prof so his lectures were dry at start of term, but improved steadily as class went on. Last few classes were my favorite. Willing to answer questions and a fair marker. Exams weren't too tough if you went to class and read the readings. Best ECO prof I've had so far. Would recommend him to others for sure.
Very helpful and took the time to answer my questions in person and online very helpful
Very helpful clear and consize One of the best teachers I had

Easiness: Aplia and Attendance are easy grades, the midterm is average difficulty, the final exam is pretty tough. Helpfulness: Responds to emails quickly, willing to adjust grades if mistakes were made. Clarity: EXTREMELY unclear in lecture. You basically have to teach yourself the course with the textbook. Not recommended for this reason.

Aplia exercises + attendance = easy 100% for 25% of your grade, but that's where the pros end. This prof cannot lecture AT ALL! I stopped listening after lecture 2 and relied on the textbook 100% for the exams. Still got an A. If it weren't for the pros mentioned in my first sentence, this would be the worst prof at uOttawa.

Such a terrible professor. I'm fairly sure he has never taught so I have no idea why he was thrown into university lectures. The only way you'll get a decent grade is by reading and understanding the entire textbook. He is useless in lecture and does not answer questions. Says he'll take attendance and has only taken it twice. STAY AWAY

He is an absolutely terrible teacher. He doesn't listen to question with any amount of care and refuses to answer questions. Pray that you never fall upon such terrible luck that you have to put up with his teaching for more than a minute.

Goes through his slides way too fast and he doesn't know what he's talking about. He NEVER properly answers a question and he could care less about your success in his class. His slides are impossible to follow and he is very unclear when he talks. Avoid him if possible!!!
